The paper presents a data-driven approach to speaker verification using neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of speech processing and recognition (cs.SD). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) as it uses text-dependent speaker verification, which could place it under the sub-category of NLP (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and optimization techniques could also place it under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper emphasizes the need for efficient and accurate systems, which could place it under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
